{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1743542527,"nonce":"NAh/8mg/alVFtCU1ZZ+rVID3iEw=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6wtDox","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6898","origin":"github"},"title":"bwa-mem2 memory update causes guaranteed OOM","message":"Following up #6890 with real-world usage:\n\nThis change causes `samtools sort` to use all of the memory allocated, which would fail even if it was running by itself since it leaves no overhead. But because `samtools sort` runs in a pipe with `bwa-mem2 mem`, it leaves no memory for bwa-mem2.\n\nI have worked around this locally with TPV by overriding `$GALAXY_MEMORY_MB` for this version of the tool by a scaling factor of 0.4. bwa-mem2 doesn't use the env var and doesn't control its memory usage, but this leaves 60% of the memory allocated for the job for bwa-mem2, which is good enough for my test case.\n\nWe should perhaps scale `$GALAXY_MEMORY_MB` in Galaxy or offer a scaled version under a different name (and the scaling factor should possibly be admin-configurable), but either way, bwa-mem2 2.2.1+galaxy3 is probably unusable as-is on any runner that sets `$GALAXY_MEMORY_MB`, and I'm not sure what we want the fix to be.","files":null}]}